always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Bromley was born in 1410, in East Peckham, Kent, England. She had at least 1 daughter with Sir John de Broughton III, of Preston. She died in 1434, in Baddington, Cheshire, England, at the age of 24."},"et":{"1410–1434":"1410–1434","1407–1489":"1407–1489","1427–Female":"1427–Surnud","1434":"1434","1489":"1489","1410":"1410","1407":"1407","Abt 1427":"umbes 1427","1427":"1427","East Peckham, Kent, England":"East Peckham, Kent, England","Broughton Moor, Cumberland, England":"Broughton Moor, Cumberland, England","Baddington, Cheshire, England":"Baddington, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"1410–1434":"1410–1434","1407–1489":"1407–1489","1427–Female":"1427–Kuollut","1434":"1434","1489":"1489","1410":"1410","1407":"1407","Abt 1427":"noin 1427","1427":"1427","East Peckham, Kent, England":"East Peckham, Kent, England","Broughton Moor, Cumberland, England":"Broughton Moor, Cumberland, England","Baddington, Cheshire, England":"Baddington, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"1410–1434":"1410–1434","1407–1489":"1407–1489","1427–Female